  "body": "## 🎉 Description\r\n\r\nTo help developers save money (and become more aware of storage costs) we should add and support (safe) bitshifts and utilities to store multiple types of data < 32bytes into one data slot \r\n\r\n- [ ] 🐛 This is a bug report.\r\n- [x ] 📈 This is a feature request.\r\n\r\n## 📝 Details\r\n\r\nAdding \r\n`SafeShiftLeft`\r\n`SafeShiftRight`\r\n`PackData()` (overloaded with various options)\r\n`UnpackData()`\r\n\r\nAmong others will allow users to pack many variables into one slot to save both gas for storage and with correct use, simplify code \r\n\r\nFor example\r\n\r\n```\r\n  getTokenData1(uint256 tokenID) returns (uint8) \r\n    return tokens[tokenID].data1;\r\n```\r\n\r\nCan be generalised into \r\n```\r\n     getTokenData(uint256 tokenID, uint256 indexOfData) returns (uint8)\r\n    return mask(tokens[tokenID], MASKS[indexOfData]);\r\n\r\n```\r\nWhere MASKs is a constant array of masks to allow for data to be masked out\r\n",
